Title: 
    MISSION IMPOSSIBLE:
    EXTREME LOVE
Draft Date: 3/14/2026

# Night 1
## Act 1

NIGHT 1 ACT 1

INT. IMF SAFE HOUSE

A simple room. A table with a tablet and an open laptop. 2 chairs. Some crates labeled IMF.
Random tech gear sitting on top of the crates - laptops, wires, binoculars, etc.
CODY is sitting at the laptop typing rapidly. He has an earpiece and is talking to someone offstage.

CODY
(into earpiece)
No, no, no, you can't just route it through any other channel! That's not how secure transmission works!
(pause)
Yes, I know you THINK it's faster. That's the problem!
(pause)
No! You can't just override the protocols!
(pause)
Then why didn't you try the backup channel?
(pause)
No, that was the coffee machine's WiFi!

The door bursts open. CALEB, ELENA, and MALCOLM enter quickly.
Elena looks irritated and fired up.

MALCOLM
Tell him he's wrong.

CODY
I'm never wrong.

ELENA
You routed the signal through the wrong channel!

CODY
That was the only channel available!

MALCOLM
Because you locked us out of the other three!

CODY
For security reasons!

ELENA
You locked us out!

CODY
Exactly!

CALEB
Alright! Time out.

They keep arguing over him.

ELENA
He compromised the mission!

CODY
You ignored the plan!

MALCOLM
The plan was flawed!

CODY
The plan was perfect!

CALEB
HEY!

They stop.

CALEB
We're on the same team, remember?
(pause)
Did we at least get the data?

CODY
Of course we got the data.
(proudly)
I got the data.

MALCOLM
WE got the data.

CODY
Mostly me.

ELENA
Barely you.

CODY
Technically—

CALEB
Cody.

Cody stops talking.

CALEB
Have you had time to analyze it?

CODY
Oh yeah.
(excited)
You're going to love this.
(gestures to the tablet)
HQ already sent the next mission.
(points to tablet)
Right there.

CALEB picks up the tablet.
Caleb taps the tablet. Lights dim slightly. Everyone turns toward the screen as the mission briefing video begins.

MISSION BRIEFING - FEMALE (V.O.)
Facial recognition complete.

MISSION BRIEFING - MALE (V.O.)
Caleb, recent intelligence gathered by your team has confirmed the existence of a mysterious device known only as “The Light.”
Little is known about the device's exact capabilities. However, intercepted communications suggest that many powerful groups are actively searching for it.
Rumors surrounding The Light include the ability to grant immense power, unimaginable wealth, or even eternal life.
While these claims remain unverified, what is certain is that the device is valuable enough that others are willing to take extreme risks to obtain it.
The device is believed to have been designed by a brilliant but unidentified figure known only as “The Architect.”
At this time, the Architect's identity and motives remain unknown.
Your mission is to locate The Light and secure it before hostile organizations can reach it first.
Due to the potential global consequences surrounding this device, strict operational protocol must be followed.
This mission will require precision, coordination, and discipline.
All agents are expected to follow established procedures and execute their roles exactly as assigned.
Deviation from mission protocol increases the likelihood of failure.
Remember:
Successful operations depend on trust in your team, respect for the chain of command, and obedience to the instructions of the designated team leader.
For this mission, Caleb has command authority.
All team members are to follow his instructions without deviation unless directed otherwise by IMF Command.
As always, if any members of your team are caught or killed, the secretary will disavow any knowledge of your actions. 
This message will self-destruct in five seconds. Good luck, Caleb.

Video ends. Lights return to normal.
The door opens and DEREK enters, carrying a tactical backpack and two juice boxes.

MALCOLM
Well… that sounded ominous.

ELENA
It sounded clear.

CODY
Clear and ominous.

DEREK
Hey guys! Sorry I'm late. I got turned around. Who wants fruit punch?

Cody, Elena, and Malcolm turn in surprise. Caleb shows no reaction.

CALEB
Cody, Elena, Malcolm, this is Derek Stone. He's Marine Special Forces — reconnaissance and counter-intelligence. Top of his class in tactical operations, expert in field surveillance and infiltration, and one of the fastest mission assessment analysts the Marines have ever produced. When things get complicated, he's the guy they'd send in to figure it out. Now he works for the IMF.

DEREK
(beaming)
And I make an excellent grilled cheese.
(offers a juice box to Malcolm)
Fruit punch?

MALCOLM
(stares at it)
I'll pass. 

DEREK
So, the instructions are: find mysterious device, secure it, and don't get caught. Got it.

ELENA
That's a very casual summary of a very serious mission.

DEREK
Relax. I work best under pressure.

CODY
You don't look like you're under pressure.

DEREK
A professional never does.

CALEB
The important part of that briefing wasn't the rumors about the device.
It was the reminder.
Missions like this only work if everyone follows the plan.

DEREK
Oh, absolutely! 100%. Protocol. Procedures. Structure.
Love all that.
Very exciting stuff.

MALCOLM
You sound a little *too* thrilled.

DEREK
I'm just eager! I mean, sometimes you have to improvise to help the team, right? You know, anticipating needs before they happen? Like the juice boxes.

Elena raises an eyebrow.

MALCOLM
That attitude is exactly how missions fall apart.

CODY
Yeah. The last time someone anticipated my needs and treated the plan like a suggestion, I spent three hours hanging upside down from a ceiling.

ELENA
You're bringing that up again?!

CODY
Three hours, Elena!

DEREK
Did it work?

CODY
Well, yes, but that's not the point…

DEREK
See? Innovation.

CALEB
Derek.
(Derek snaps to attention.)
The reason we follow instructions is because each of us individually don't always see the whole picture. We have to trust those in authority over us to give us the best information and the best plan.

DEREK
Got it. Obey the plan. Trust HQ. No improvising.

Elena and Cody exchange a look.

CALEB
Alright.
Cody, gather everything we have on The Architect.
Elena, start mapping possible locations where this device could be hidden.
Derek—
(Derek salutes awkwardly.)
Stay ready. We'll brief the full operation once we have more intel.

DEREK
Copy that.
I'll be… extremely ready.

CODY
That confidence is either comforting or terrifying.

They begin gathering around the table reviewing maps and data.

===

## Act 2

NIGHT 1 ACT 2

INT. SERVER VAULT - NIGHT

A dimly lit, high-security server room. Racks of blinking equipment hum quietly.
At the end of the room sits a TERMINAL on a pedestal.
The floor between the entrance and the terminal is divided into square panels.
Only one path across the floor is safe.
Derek stands at the entrance to the grid, studying the floor.

In his ear, the team speaks over comms.

CODY (V.O.)
Alright Derek, you should be looking at a grid of floor panels.

DEREK
I see it.

CODY (V.O.)
Each square is pressure sensitive. Step on the wrong one and the vault triggers a security protocol.

DEREK
And the Light relocates. Got it.

CALEB (V.O.)
Derek, Malcolm has the path on the tablet. Follow his instructions exactly.

DEREK
Copy that.

CODY (V.O.)
And Derek?

DEREK
Yeah?

CODY (V.O.)
Try not to step on the wrong ones.

DEREK
Comforting.

MALCOLM (V.O.)
Alright. First step — forward two squares.

Derek moves carefully. His steps are precise and controlled.

MALCOLM (V.O.)
Now one to your left.

Derek steps.

MALCOLM (V.O.)
Forward one.

DEREK
You know, this would be a lot easier if I had the tablet.

CODY (V.O.)
We went over that already. The tablet has to be directly connected to the mainframe.

MALCOLM (V.O.)
Derek, stay focused. Next step forward.

Derek steps again.

INT. ELECTRICAL CLOSET - SAME TIME

Elena stands at an open electrical JUNCTION BOX in the wall, holding a small flashlight and wire cutters.

ELENA
I found the secondary relay. It's a mess in here.

CALEB (V.O.)
Stand by, Elena.

INT. SERVER VAULT - CONTINUOUS

Derek reaches the middle of the grid.
Suddenly a faint mechanical WHIRRING is heard.

DEREK
Uh... Malcolm?

MALCOLM (V.O.)
I see it.

CODY (V.O.)
That's not good.

DEREK
Let me guess.

MALCOLM (V.O.)
Security pattern just changed.

CALEB (V.O.)
That wasn't supposed to happen yet.

CODY (V.O.)
They must have accelerated the vault cycle.

CALEB (V.O.)
Cody, can you delay it?

CODY (V.O.)
Not from here! Elena, I need you to do the hard reset. Cut the green wire in the relay.

INT. ELECTRICAL CLOSET - CONTINUOUS

Elena pulls a thick bundle of identical wires out of the box.

ELENA
Cody, they're all green.

CODY (V.O.)
They aren't all green! One is lime, one is emerald, one is forest-

ELENA
(cutting him off)
I am holding a dozen completely identical green cords.
(fingering through the wires)
I'm going to have to guess.

CODY (V.O.)
If you cut the wrong one, you'll drop the whole grid! 

ELENA
I'm guessing.

CODY (V.O.)
Wait, no-!

Elena SNIPS a wire. A small spark jumps.
A moment of tension.

INT. SERVER VAULT - CONTINUOUS

Derek studies the floor ahead of him. The vault hums steadily.
No alarms.

CODY (V.O.)
Good guess, Elena! That bought us a few more seconds.

CALEB (V.O.)
Keep holding position, Derek.

DEREK
Holding.

CALEB (V.O.)
Cody almost has it.

Derek studies the floor again.
He spots the final square near the terminal.
A long gap between where he stands and the last safe panel.

DEREK
Caleb… I'm only a about 6 feet from the terminal.

CALEB (V.O.)
Stay where you are.

DEREK
If I jump the last panel I can clear the grid.

CALEB (V.O.)
Negative. It's too far.

CODY (V.O.)
Almost there… almost there…

Derek crouches slightly, calculating the distance.

CALEB (V.O.)
Derek, if you miss at all the Light will be moved and we'll have nothing.

CODY (V.O.)
Just a few more seconds!

DEREK
We're out of time.
(beat)
I'm going for it.

CALEB (V.O.)
No, wait!

Derek leaps across the grid.
His boot lands on the final square.
For a split second his heel presses down on the wrong panel.[[need to make clear that he's stepping on the wrong one]]
But—
Nothing happens.
No alarms.
No lights.
Derek smirks slightly.

DEREK
Told you.

He walks to the terminal and begins typing.

MALCOLM (V.O.)
What's happening?

CODY (V.O.)
I've got it!

DEREK
I'm already here. Plugging in now.
(he inserts the secure drive)
Starting the download.
(pause)
It's running.

CODY (V.O.)
Wait something is wrong.

CALEB (V.O.)
What?

DEREK
20%.

CODY (V.O.)
Someone else is in the system.

ELENA (V.O.)
What? Who?

CODY (V.O.)
I don't know! I don't know! Derek what's happening?

DEREK
It's at 32% but the bar stopped moving.

ELENA (V.O.)
We have company.

CALEB (V.O.)
Cody, what's going on?

CODY (V.O.)
Hang on...
(beat)
There it is!
The alarm was triggered silently.

CALEB (V.O.)
Which alarm?

CODY (V.O.)
The floor alarm! The one we were supposed to avoid by following directions!
(pause-keyboard sounds)
The Light is being moved.

Derek stares at the screen as warning messages appear.

DEREK
Uh... I've got errors coming up on the screen now.

The download bar suddenly disappears.

CODY (V.O.)
The server is relocating The Light!

CALEB (V.O.)
Derek, pull the drive and get out of there.
This mission is over.

Derek yanks the drive from the terminal.

DEREK
Copy.

He moves quickly across the room and exits.

INT. ELECTRICAL CLOSET - SAME TIME

Elena steps away from the smoking junction box.

ELENA
I'm clear. Moving out.

TRANSITION TO:

INT. IMF SAFE HOUSE - LATER

The team gathers around the main table.
Tension fills the room.
Cody studies the laptop.

CODY
It's gone.

Derek stands quietly.

CALEB
Walk me through it.

DEREK
The floor pattern changed halfway through.

ELENA
Which is why we needed the delay.

DEREK
I had a clear shot to the final square. I took it.

MALCOLM
And triggered the alarm.

Derek exhales.

DEREK
It didn't trigger immediately.

CODY
No.
(beat)
It waited until the transfer started.

MALCOLM
Which means the vault recorded the wrong step... and moved the Light the moment we accessed the system.

Silence.

CALEB
Derek, your jump almost worked.

Derek looks up, surprised.

CALEB (CONT'D)
But the mission wasn't yours to redesign.
(beat)
We had a plan.
We had instructions.
And every part of that mission depended on everyone following them exactly.

Derek nods slowly.

CALEB (CONT'D)
When we start deciding our own way is better... that's when things fall apart.
And tonight, your disobedience lost us the Light.

===

# Night 2

## Act 1

NIGHT 2 ACT 1

INT. IMF SAFE HOUSE - NIGHT

The team gathers around the central table. A laptop and tablet sit open, displaying maps, code, and fragments of data.
Cody types furiously on the laptop. Elena stands nearby, arms crossed, watching the screen.
Caleb studies the tablet.
Derek leans casually against a crate.

CODY
I'm telling you, the vault security didn't just move the program randomly. There's a relocation pattern.

MALCOLM
And I'm telling you that pattern doesn't matter if we can't predict where it's going next.

CODY
Of course it matters. Patterns always matter.

MALCOLM
Unless the system adapts.

CODY
It's software, Malcolm. Software follows rules.

MALCOLM
Not if someone designed it not to.

CODY
That would be ridiculous.

MALCOLM
Would it?

DEREK
This is fascinating. Really. But are we planning the next mission or hosting a debate club?

CODY
I'm planning the mission.

ELENA
You're guessing.

CODY
I am not guessing.

MALCOLM
You literally just said “probably.”

CODY
That was a strategic “probably.”

DEREK
(holding up a bag)
Hey guys, I brought tactical trail mix. Anyone want some M&Ms? It helps with tension. I ate all the brown ones already.

ELENA
Not now, Derek.

CALEB
Enough.

They quiet down.

CALEB (CONT'D)
We lost the Light once. We're not doing that again.

Derek nods slightly.

CALEB (CONT'D)
Cody, what do we know?

CODY
The Light relocated immediately after the floor alarm triggered.

He gestures to the screen.

CODY (CONT'D)
The program moved to another server in the network, but the trail goes cold after that.

ELENA
Meaning someone hid it.

CODY
Meaning someone knew we were there.

Derek straightens a little.

DEREK
We already knew we weren't the only ones looking for it.

Suddenly the laptop screen flickers.
The lights on the equipment blink.
CODY freezes.

CODY
...that's not good.

ELENA
What did you do?

CODY
I didn't do anything!

The screen goes dark.
Then a new message appears.
A distorted voice fills the room.

THE NULL (V.O.)
You were closer than I expected.

The team looks up at the screen.

THE NULL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
That usually makes failure harder to accept.

CODY
Someone's in our system.

MALCOLM
Obviously.

CALEB steps forward.

CALEB
Who are you?

THE NULL (V.O.)
A witness.
If you need a name… call me the Null.

DEREK
(scoffing)
Subtle.

THE NULL (V.O.)
Not really.
Subtle would have been letting you believe the vault was your only mistake.

CODY
You triggered the relocation.

Derek stiffens slightly.

THE NULL (V.O.)
I accelerated it.
You triggered it.
There is a difference.
You were told to hold position.
You jumped.
You nearly succeeded.
That is what makes disobedience so useful.
It feels wise right up until everything falls apart.

CALEB
Why are you contacting us?

THE NULL (V.O.)
Because I wanted to see whether the failure had done its work.

Cody begins typing rapidly.
Malcolm leans over the keyboard.

MALCOLM
Move.

CODY
I'm tracing him.

MALCOLM
Not on that port.

CODY
Don't start.

MALCOLM
Then stop missing relays.

He reaches in and types something.
Cody watches, annoyed, then keeps going.

THE NULL (V.O.)
There it is.
The blame, the backbiting.
You save me so much time.

CODY
I'm tracing the signal.
I can find you.

THE NULL (V.O.)
Can you?
Or will he have to correct you again?

MALCOLM
Keep talking.

THE NULL (V.O.)
Gladly.
Derek thinks the plan failed him.
Cody thinks Derek cost him the Light.
Malcolm and Elena think Cody's pride keeps making things worse.
And Caleb...
(beat)
Caleb is wondering whether any of you can be trusted with the next move.

The room goes still for a moment.

CALEB
You're trying to divide us.

THE NULL (V.O.)
Trying?
No.
I'm simply saying out loud what failure already whispered.

DEREK
You don't know this team.

THE NULL (V.O.)
I know enough.
You are not hard to read.
One ignored instruction, one bruised ego, one argument at the keyboard...
and the mission collapses.

CALEB
What do you want?

THE NULL (V.O.)
The Light of course.

Cody slams a key.

CODY
Almost got him.

MALCOLM
No, that's a loop. He's feeding us a false trace.

CODY
What?

THE NULL (V.O.)
Yes.
And you took it immediately.

The screen flickers again.

THE NULL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
That is the trouble with deception.
People usually help it along.

ELENA
Then I guess we're still in the race.

THE NULL (V.O.)
No, Elena.
You're in each other's way.
(pause)
Goodbye, agents.

The screen goes black.
Silence.
CODY keeps typing.

CODY
Come on… come on…

He stops.

CODY (CONT'D)
He's gone.

CALEB
Did you get anything?

CODY exhales.

CODY
Whoever that was masked the signal behind about twelve layers of encryption and bounced it through half the internet.
So technically yes… I traced it.

DEREK
To where?

CODY
Everywhere.

MALCOLM
Meaning nowhere.

CODY
(snapping at Malcolm)
Meaning he's untraceable! You didn't do any better!

Derek folds his arms.

DEREK
So he didn't just bait the trace.
He baited us.

MALCOLM
And he was counting on this exact reaction.

ELENA
Then maybe we should stop taking the bait.

Derek gives her a look.

DEREK
Go ahead. Say it.

CALEB steps forward.

CALEB
Enough.

The room quiets.

CALEB (CONT'D)
Listen to yourselves.
He didn't break into our system just to threaten us.
He came here to accuse, deceive, and divide.
And for a minute, we let him.

He looks at his team.

CALEB (CONT'D)
That ends now.
This mission just changed.
We're not just chasing the Light.
We're up against someone who knows he can't beat a united team, so he'll keep trying to split us apart.

DEREK
So what do we do?

CALEB
We close the gaps. And that starts with forgiveness. 
God calls us to forgive each other, especially when we mess up. If we hold onto this bitterness, the Null has already won.

Silence. The tension in the room is palpable.
Cody and Malcolm step further apart.
Elena exchanges a glare with Derek.

MALCOLM
Look, Caleb. I'm a professional. We can work together. But I'm not going to forgive him.

CODY
Right. The mission comes first. We'll just... focus on the mission.

CALEB
Ignoring it isn't fixing it. You can't just 'work together' when there's a wall between you.

DEREK
(quietly)
He's right, you know.

ELENA
(sharp)
Let's just prep the next phase.

They turn back to the monitors, avoiding each other. The tension is still heavy.

FADE OUT.

===

[[Maybe during the transmission, Cody can tell Caleb that he figured out why he couldn't trace the hack - because it wasn't a hack. it was a virus - an artificial intelligence was talking to them.]]

===

## Act 2

NIGHT 2 ACT 2

INT. RESEARCH FACILITY CORRIDOR - NIGHT

A sterile hallway washed in low red security light.
At the far end stands a sealed BIOMETRIC DOOR labeled COMPUTER CORE.
CALEB kneels beside the scanner, one hand on his earpiece, eyes locked on the door.
`
Elsewhere in the building, CODY, MALCOLM, and ELENA work separate angles over comms.
Somewhere deeper inside, DEREK moves alone through the facility.

CALEB
Status.

CODY (V.O.)
You're at the right door. Palm scanner on the left, keypad on the right?

CALEB
That's what I'm looking at.

MALCOLM (V.O.)
Then give me thirty seconds.

CODY (V.O.)
You wouldn't need thirty seconds if you hadn't ruined the original hand print.

MALCOLM (V.O.)
I didn't ruin it. Your timing algorithm was off, so I adapted.

CODY (V.O.)
My timing was exact.

CALEB
Both of you. Focus.

DEREK (V.O.)
Checkpoint four clear.
The duct maze was disgusting, the laser hall was rude, and I would like that noted in the mission report.

CODY (V.O.)
Noted.
Keep moving.

CALEB
Next checkpoint in sixty seconds, Derek.

DEREK (V.O.)
See? I'm checking in.
Personal growth.

CALEB steps closer to the door.
As he does, the DOOR UNIT slowly pivots out from the back wall, revealing the COMPUTER ROOM on the opposite side to the audience.
Inside: a dark room, a glowing console, and a wall monitor mirroring the computer display.
Caleb cannot see any of it yet.

INT. COMPUTER ROOM - SAME TIME

Above the console, a ceiling panel silently opens.
A FIGURE DRESSED IN BLACK lowers on a cable and lands beside the machine.

INT. RESEARCH FACILITY CORRIDOR - CONTINUOUS

DEREK (V.O.)
Crossing the west stairwell now. Should hit checkpoint five in twenty.

CALEB
Report the moment you get there.

DEREK (V.O.)
Copy that.

INT. COMPUTER ROOM - SAME TIME

The figure plugs a device into the computer.
The wall monitor lights up: ACCESSING ARCHIVE.

INT. RESEARCH FACILITY CORRIDOR - CONTINUOUS

CODY (V.O.)
Malcolm, send the print.

MALCOLM (V.O.)
Working on it.

CODY (V.O.)
That is not the same as sending it.

MALCOLM (V.O.)
Because unlike you, I prefer accuracy.

CODY (V.O.)
Unlike you, I prefer the part where the plan still works.

A beat.

CALEB
Derek, checkpoint five.

Silence.

CALEB (CONT'D)
Derek?

CODY (V.O.)
He's probably still moving.

CALEB
Derek, respond.

Static crackles.

DEREK (V.O.)
(out of breath)
Still here.
Took a detour around a patrol.
I'm at checkpoint fi-

A sudden struggle erupts over comms.
A sharp grunt. A metallic crash.
Then heavy static.

DEREK (V.O.) (CONT'D)
Caleb-

The channel cuts out.

CALEB
Derek? Derek!

No answer.

INT. COMPUTER ROOM - SAME TIME

The transfer bar climbs: 18%... 31%.

INT. RESEARCH FACILITY CORRIDOR - CONTINUOUS

ELENA (V.O.)
I heard it.

CODY (V.O.)
So did I.

CALEB
Elena, where are you?

ELENA (V.O.)
One corridor over from the security office.

CALEB
Go find Derek.
Malcolm, get me the print.
Cody, get this door open now.

CODY (V.O.)
Trying.

A chime hits Caleb's phone.

CODY (V.O.) (CONT'D)
You should have the file.

Caleb raises the phone to the scanner.
The reader flashes red.

CALEB
No good.

CODY (V.O.)
What?
No, no, no, that should have taken.

MALCOLM (V.O.)
Because the system wants a full print, not your fake approval packet.

CODY (V.O.)
My fake approval packet is the only reason this has any chance of working!

MALCOLM (V.O.)
If you had trusted my bypass, I would've had the real print ten minutes ago.

CODY (V.O.)
If you had followed my sequence, the first print wouldn't be useless!

CALEB
Enough!

He slaps the phone down against his leg, forcing calm.

CALEB (CONT'D)
We do not have time for this.
Malcolm, send it again.
Cody, when it comes through, make it work.

INT. COMPUTER ROOM - SAME TIME

The wall monitor climbs: 46%... 57%.

INT. RESEARCH FACILITY CORRIDOR - CONTINUOUS

Derek's channel stays dead.

CALEB
Derek, report.

Only static.

MALCOLM (V.O.)
Sending a fresh scan now.

CODY (V.O.)
Wait - don't send while I'm rewriting the handshake-

The file arrives.

CODY (V.O.) (CONT'D)
Too late.

MALCOLM (V.O.)
Then rewrite faster.

CODY (V.O.)
That is not how coding works!

CALEB closes his eyes for half a second.

CALEB
Cody.

CODY (V.O.)
Right.
Working.

A tense beat.
Caleb watches the corridor behind him, then the locked door.

Another chime.

CALEB
Got it.
(raises phone to scanner)
Great, Malcolm. Elena, how close are you to Derek?

ELENA (V.O.)
Almost there.

The scanner reads.
Red light.

CALEB
Cody, it's not working.

INT. COMPUTER ROOM - SAME TIME

The figure in black reaches 79% and types another command.

INT. RESEARCH FACILITY CORRIDOR - CONTINUOUS

CODY (V.O.)
Ok, hold on, hold on!
(keyboard sounds)
Ok, try it now!

Caleb scans again.
Green light.
A click from the biometric lock.

CALEB
It worked.
There's a password too.

CODY (V.O.)
Intel didn't say anything about a password!
Ok hang on.
I'm already in this, shouldn't be too difficult.

INT. COMPUTER ROOM - SAME TIME

The figure ejects the device and disconnects it.
The transfer completes.
On the screen, one line appears: NULL ACCESS CONFIRMED.

The figure starts ascending toward the ceiling.

INT. RESEARCH FACILITY CORRIDOR - CONTINUOUS

CALEB waits, jaw tight.

CALEB
Cody.

CODY (V.O.)
Almost there...
almost there...
Ok, the password is 7-0-x-7.

Caleb types the code.
The door unlocks.

INT. COMPUTER ROOM - CONTINUOUS

Caleb bursts into the room just as the ceiling panel slides shut above him.
A cable swings slightly in the air.

He crosses to the console and types.
His face falls.

CALEB
(into comms)
Someone just wiped the files.

CODY (V.O.)
What?

Caleb studies the access log.

ON THE SCREEN:
LAST USER: NULL

CALEB
He left his signature.
It was the Null.

He looks up at the seam in the ceiling.

CALEB (CONT'D)
He came in from above.

ELENA (V.O.)
Caleb...

She sounds different now. Breathless.

CALEB
Report.

ELENA (V.O.)
I found checkpoint five.
Derek isn't here.
There's no sign of him.

CODY (V.O.)
Derek, if you can hear us, answer.

Silence.

ELENA (V.O.)
Wait...I found something. 
It's Derek's earpiece, and it's sitting on what looks like a playing card, except it's completely black.

CALEB
The Null. He must have captured him.

ELENA (V.O.)
But why?

CALEB
Everyone, fall back to the safe house.

TRANSITION TO:

INT. IMF SAFE HOUSE - LATER

The room is quieter than usual.
No one leans against the wall. No one jokes from the corner.
Derek's absence hangs over the whole space.

Cody sits at the laptop, exhausted.
Malcolm and Elena stand nearby, tense and still.
Caleb remains at the head of the table.

CODY
I pulled everything I could from the terminal.
The Null got there first, took the archive, and wiped the system before Caleb got through the door.

ELENA
And Derek's tracker went dark at checkpoint five.
No cameras. No usable prints. Nothing.

CODY looks down.

CODY
So we lost the Light.
Again.

No one answers.

CALEB
The Null didn't beat us at that door.
He beat us before I ever touched the scanner.
He got us looking at each other like the enemy.

Cody and Malcolm both know he's right.

CALEB (CONT'D)
I told you earlier that we needed to forgive each other, and you thought you could just push through it safely. Look where that got us.
We can't do this on our own strength. We're too stubborn. We need to rely on God's grace. He forgave us when we didn't deserve it, and He's asking us to do the same for each other.

A long beat. The weight of Caleb's words, and Derek's absence, settles on them.
Caleb walks to the other side of the room and looks at a tablet.
Malcolm tries to go back to work on a laptop.
Cody tries to keep working but stops. He picks up a BIBLE on the table and turns to Matthew 18:21.
He reads verses 21-27.

CODY
(to himself)
"[Mat 18:21-27 NLT] 21 Then Peter came to him and asked, "Lord, how often should I forgive someone who sins against me? Seven times?" 22 "No, not seven times," Jesus replied, "but seventy times seven! 23 "Therefore, the Kingdom of Heaven can be compared to a king who decided to bring his accounts up to date with servants who had borrowed money from him. 24 In the process, one of his debtors was brought in who owed him millions of dollars. 25 He couldn't pay, so his master ordered that he be sold--along with his wife, his children, and everything he owned--to pay the debt. 26 "But the man fell down before his master and begged him, 'Please, be patient with me, and I will pay it all.' 27 Then his master was filled with pity for him, and he released him and forgave his debt."
(closing the Bible)
Lord, you've forgiven me so much. Help me let this small petty disagreement go.
(turns to Malcolm)
Malcolm... 

Malcolm looks up from where he is.
Elena and Caleb also look.

CODY (CONT'D)
I was so busy proving my plan was better that I stopped listening. I cared more about being right than helping you. It was pride, and it cost us Derek. I'm sorry.

MALCOLM meets his eyes.

MALCOLM
(voice steady but softened)
Honestly, I changed the hand print bypass because I thought your code was flawed.
I didn't tell anyone until it was already broken.
(beat)
I kept fighting you because I didn't want to admit I was wrong. I'm sorry too.

Elena, feeling left out, steps forward awkwardly.

ELENA
I'm sorry too, guys!

MALCOLM
What are you sorry for?

ELENA
I don't know! For judging you both? 
(pause)
Honestly, it just felt like we were having a really deep team moment and I panicked.
(pause)
But I am sorry.

CALEB
Alright, isn't that better. Now, hug it out.

Cody and Malcolm look at Caleb with a glare.

CODY
I don't think so, boss.

MALCOLM^
Not happening.

ELENA^
Ya, no.

CALEB
No?
(looks at all of them)
Alright, look. When we rely on God to heal these fractures, the Null loses his greatest weapon against us.

He looks at the empty place where Derek would usually stand.

CALEB (CONT'D)
Tonight he took the Light.
And he took Derek.

The weight of that lands.

CALEB (CONT'D)
We can't change tonight by blaming each other.
But we can decide what kind of team we are when the next mission starts.

ELENA
(awkwardly)
A better one!

Everyone gives her a look.
Cody turns to his laptop with renewed energy.

CODY
I'll start scanning for communication black spots. The Null has to be holding him somewhere.

Malcolm brings his laptop over and sits next to him.

MALCOLM
I'll help you rebuild the tracking algorithm. We can cross-reference the local networks.

Cody looks at Malcolm, surprised but grateful. 

CODY
Let's do it.

Caleb looks at his team, fully united for the first time. He gives a firm nod.

CALEB
Until we know otherwise, Derek is alive.
And tomorrow, we are bringing him home.

FADE OUT.

===

# Night 3

## Act 1

NIGHT 3 ACT 1

INT. IMF SAFE HOUSE - NIGHT

Only moments later.
The room looks the same, but the energy is completely different.
Cody is still at the laptop, pulling up whatever traces he can.
Malcolm stands behind him, arms crossed, staring intently at the screen.
Elena paces near the table.
Caleb stands still, staring at the empty place where Derek should be.

CODY
I really hate saying this out loud...
(beat)
this guy is good.

MALCOLM
He got in and out of a sealed computer room, stole the Light, and left almost nothing behind.

CALEB
He's more than a hacker.
He had to know the building, the timing, the entry point, and our response window.
Whoever the Null is, he's smart enough to break the system and skilled enough to move through it.

CODY
Which is an extremely dangerous combination.

ELENA stops pacing.

ELENA
And now he has the Light.

CALEB turns toward the table.
Something catches his eye.

A TABLET sits beside the laptop.
Same model as before.

CALEB
Cody.
Malcolm.
Was that here before?

Cody looks up.

CODY
No.

MALCOLM
I didn't bring it.

Caleb picks it up carefully.
The screen is black.
He taps the screen.
Lights dim slightly.

MISSION BRIEFING - MALE (V.O.)
Facial recognition complete. Hello Caleb.

CODY
That was a lot less comforting this time.

The screen brightens.
At first, it looks and sounds exactly like a standard IMF message.

MISSION BRIEFING - MALE (V.O.)
Your team failed to secure the Light. This is unacceptable.
You were given a clear objective, and you failed to complete it.
A hostile party took the asset before your team could secure it.
That failure has compromised the mission and escalated the threat.
(pause)
I'm honestly surprised how easy it was to completely break your team.

CODY
(interrupting)
That's awfully personal for a mission briefing.

MISSION BRIEFING - MALE (V.O.) (CONT'D)
You'll need to work together much better than that if you ever want to see your friend Derek again.

Elena, Cody, and Malcolm exchange a quick look.

ELENA
What is this? Where did this message come from?

MALCOLM
Cody, where did this come from?

Cody moves toward the laptop and starts typing, but there is no response from the message.

MISSION BRIEFING - MALE (V.O.) (CONT'D)
Even though you lost the Light, your mission is not over.
Possession of the Light does not mean control of it.
The Light is encrypted. Only someone with the access code can unlock it.

The screen flickers.
The lights dim.
The screen and voice changes to the NULL.

THE NULL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
And you are going to find it for me.

CODY
It's from the Null.

THE NULL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
Before you start imagining a way out of this.
The last time you failed, you lost the Light.
This time, you'll lose a friend.

Caleb's expression hardens.

THE NULL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
Bring me the code, and Derek goes free.
Refuse me, delay me, or attempt anything creative...
and you'll never see your teammate again.

Cody stops typing for just a second.

THE NULL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
Do not comfort yourselves with the thought that I am bluffing.
You have already seen how quickly one wrong move can cost you.
Your mission, whether you choose to accept it or not, is to recover my code.
Try not to fail this mission the way you failed the last two.
(pause)
I think you'll find you have all you need.

The screen goes black.
Lights return to normal.

No one speaks for a beat.

CODY
I hate him.

ELENA
How do we know he's not lying?
We didn't see Derek.
We didn't hear him.

CALEB
We don't. But what choice do we have?

CODY
He wasn't kidding about the code.

ELENA
Meaning?

CODY
Meaning the Light is locked tight.
Like stealing a safe without the combination.
He can carry it around all he wants, but he still can't get what's inside.

ELENA
And if we get the code for him, we hand him exactly what he needs.

CODY
Pretty much, yes.

ELENA
Then why would we help him?

CALEB
We don't help him.
We move before he does.

Elena looks at him.

CALEB (CONT'D)
If Derek is with him, we bring Derek home.
If the code is real, we secure it before the Null can use it.

MALCOLM
So we're accepting a mission from the guy who stole our mission.

CALEB
We're taking back control of it.

ELENA
And if we find the Null first?

Caleb looks at both of them.

CALEB
Then we stop him.

CODY
Where do we even start?

CALEB
This tablet. I doubt we'll find much, but it's the only lead we have.
He touched it, he loaded the message onto it, and he left it here.
Maybe we can find something that leads us to him.

MALCOLM
What about the decryption code? "You have all you need." What did he mean by that?

CODY
Let me see the tablet.

Cody takes the tablet and taps away on it for a few moments.
Lines of data scroll rapidly across the screen.

CODY (CONT'D)
He wiped most of the metadata, but he left an encoded packet in the partition.
(typing)
Got it. It's coordinates. An abandoned warehouse on the edge of the city.

ELENA
That's the handoff point. He's inviting us to come to him.

CALEB
He expects us to walk in with the code for the Light. But we don't have it.

The team pauses to think.

CODY
If "the Architect" built the Light, he must have built the cipher too. Does the IMF have any intel on him?

MALCOLM
We have archives. Ancient manuscripts and old case files going back centuries. If the cipher exists, it might be buried in there.

CALEB
Cody, Malcolm, start digging through those archives. Find everything you can on the Architect. 

ELENA
And the coordinates?

CALEB
He wants a trade, but I have another idea.

Caleb walks out of the room.

MALCOLM
Is he going to tell us his idea?

Elena and Cody look at each other and shrug, then get to work.

FADE OUT.

===

## Activity Briefing

/* 
After Bible Story and before the kids start their activities, the team receives a transmission from Caleb.
*/

ACTIVITY BRIEFING (Video Transmission)

CALEB
Team, the Light is locked tight. It cannot be hacked — we absolutely need the decryption code.
The good news is Cody and Malcolm found a fragmented cypher hidden deep within a set of ancient manuscripts tied to the Architect. We believe it may contain the decryption code, but it needs to be deciphered. I need your groups to decrypt the decryption code for us.
The Null gave us coordinates for the handoff at an abandoned warehouse. He expects us to bring him the code in exchange for Derek.
But we aren't going to play his game. Instead of giving the Null what he wants, we are going in to rescue our teammate. 
The infiltration timing is tricky, and I'll have to access the warehouse from the roof. I need you to set up a tactical training course so we can practice the route and time it perfectly. I'll have to cross a narrow ledge between adjacent buildings, slide down a set of suspended electrical wires, and crawl through the ventilation duct-work to get inside. 
Once I'm in, the holding cell is guarded by a high-security laser grid. I'm hoping our team can work together to shut those lasers down remotely. But if they can't, I need to know it's possible to navigate the grid manually. I need you to practice that for me.
You have a lot of work to do, agents. Remember, we aren't doing this on our own. Rely on God for your strength, and I know you'll do great. I'll leave you to it.

===

## Act 2

NIGHT 3 ACT 2

INT. THE NULL'S BASE - NIGHT

A high-tech corridor bathed in blue light. The path forward is blocked by a dense grid of glowing red LASERS. 
At the far end of the corridor sits a heavy reinforced door—the HOLDING CELL.

CALEB stands at the edge of the laser grid. He taps his earpiece.

CALEB
I made it to the grid. It's active.

CODY (V.O.)
I see it. The system is heavily fortified. Malcolm, are you tied into the primary relay?

MALCOLM (V.O.)
Tied in and holding. Elena, status?

ELENA (V.O.)
Locked onto the secondary mainframe. Awaiting your mark, Cody.

CODY (V.O.)
Okay. The only way through is if Malcolm, Elena, and I drop the laser modules in sequence. We have a three-second window for each section before the system resets.

CALEB
Just like the floor grid. Only this time, we do it together. Tell me when.

CODY (V.O.)
Malcolm, drop the lower grid in 3... 2... 1... Mark.

MALCOLM (V.O.)
Lower grid down. Go, Caleb!

Caleb steps forward, ducking under a high laser.

CODY (V.O.)
Resetting in 2... 1... Taking control of the middle grid. Dropping now!

Caleb steps precisely through the opening.

CALEB
I'm through the middle. One more section.

ELENA (V.O.)
I've got the final matrix. Dropping it... now!

Caleb makes one final deliberate move and clears the grid entirely. 
The lasers behind him immediately hum back to life.

CALEB
I'm clear. I'm at the cell door. Excellent work, team.

CODY (V.O.)
See what happens when nobody goes rogue? I'm hacking the lock now.

MALCOLM (V.O.)
Wait. Cody... the security protocols in my wing just engaged.

CODY (V.O.)
What? No, that's impossible, I disabled those-- 

ELENA (V.O.)
My blast doors just triggered too!

CALEB
Cody? Malcolm? Elena? What's happening?

Over comms, SIRENS blare.

MALCOLM (V.O.)
Someone's overriding the system! Oxygen is venting!

CODY (V.O.)
It's the Null! He locked us in! Caleb, you have to--

Static. The comms go dead.

CALEB
Cody! Malcolm! Elena!

The lights in the Decryption Core suddenly shut off. 
A single spotlight illuminates the center of the room.

THE NULL steps out from the shadows, dressed entirely in black, wearing a featureless mask.

THE NULL
They are out of time, Caleb.

Caleb slowly turns around to face him.

CALEB
Let them go.

THE NULL
You were instructed to bring the decryption code. Instead, you attempt a rescue. A foolish mistake. Now I have the leverage to ensure I get what I want. Hand over the code, or your friends won't make it out of those rooms.

Caleb stares at him. He reaches into his jacket and pulls out a secure drive. He tosses it to The Null.

CALEB
The Light isn't what you think it is... Derek.

The Null freezes.
Slowly, he reaches up and pulls off the mask.
It is DEREK. No longer goofy. His expression is cold and arrogant.

DEREK
How did you know it was me?

CALEB
The tablet in the safe house. No one could have planted that unless they already had access. We were supposed to be searching for a ghost, but the real threat was standing right next to us.

DEREK
(smirks)
And yet, you still walked right into my trap. You were so desperate to save your teammate that you handed over the only thing that matters.

Derek steps over to a laptop in the corner and plugs in the drive.
Instead of decrypting the Light, the drive deactivates Derek's security, releasing Cody, Malcolm and Elena.

CALEB
Actually, Derek, you just took the bait. 

Derek looks confused.

CALEB (CONT'D)
That drive isn't the key.

Derek examines the drive, realizing he's been played. He turns to bolt. 
Before making it out the door, he runs directly into CODY, ELENA, and MALCOLM.
They stand perfectly fine, arms crossed.

Derek is shocked.

CODY
Glad to see my virus worked.

DEREK
How-- I locked you in! The comms...

ELENA
You thought you locked us in.

MALCOLM
We can be a pretty clever team when we work together.

CALEB steps up behind Derek.

CALEB
The comms were faked. We knew you were listening. 
When you realize the enemy's game plan, you don't fight each other. 
You work together to subvert it.

Malcolm and Cody grab Derek by the arms, securing him. 
Derek struggles for a second, then stops, glaring at them.

DEREK
You set me up.

ELENA
You used us. You tore this team apart just to serve yourself.

MALCOLM
And now you're going to pay for it. I'm going to make sure IMF locks you in a cell so deep you'll never see light again.

CODY
Justice. I love it.
(turns to Caleb)
Caleb, do you have the real decryption code?

Caleb reaches into his jacket and pulls out a secure drive.

CALEB
Our brilliant team back at HQ cracked the decryption code.

He steps over to the central laptop and plugs it in.
The code that they discovered when doing the activity shows up on the screen.
It appears to be a jumble of random letters with no meaning.
Caleb tries to unlock the Light using the code, but it doesn't work.

CODY
It didn't work. Why didn't it work?

The team paces and contemplates while looking at the screen.

MALCOLM
I know they decrypted those codes correctly. I double-checked the work myself.

ELENA
Maybe there's one last puzzle. Look at the spaces in the code.

CODY
Right, like they are supposed to be words. But they aren't jumbled.

MALCOLM
Maybe a cipher.

DEREK
(annoyed)
Ugh, another cipher.

ELENA
(to Derek)
You shut it!

CALEB
Maybe the letters are just shifted by some number. 
Let's see.

Caleb types on the laptop. A terminal pops up. Some code is written. When he hits [ENTER], the code starts quickly cycling through hundreds of seemingly random combinations before finally stopping on a readable sentence.
The screen displays: **Then God said Let there be light and there was light**

CODY
The code is a Bible verse?

DEEP SOOTHING MALE VOICE (V.O.)
Passcode accepted. Decryption complete. The Light is unlocked.

The terminal screen proceeds to display a short video.
The voice recites a few Bible verses. 
It explains that life is full of impossible missions that are only possible with the Spirit of God.
It reminds us that obedience to God's Word is essential even when it conflicts with our own desires.
It reminds us that no matter how hurtful someone has been to us, we must forgive, since we have been forgiven so much more.
It reminds us that we are to show extreme love - even to our enemies.

When the video ends, Caleb looks back at Derek. He is still held securely by Cody and Malcolm. He looks angry and defeated.

CALEB
Love... your enemies.

Caleb stands from the laptop and walks over to Derek.

CALEB (CONT'D)
Derek, you deserve punishment. You betrayed us.
But Romans says that *while we were still sinners*, Christ died for us.
Not after we cleaned ourselves up.
Not after we earned it.
While we were still His enemies.

CODY
Caleb, are you saying we're going to let him go?

CALEB
No.
He still deserves justice.
But Jesus didn't tell us to love our enemies because they deserve it.
He told us to love them because that's how He loved us.

MALCOLM
After everything he's done?

CALEB
Especially after everything he's done.

Derek lets out a short, bitter laugh.

DEREK
This is pathetic.
You finally win and now you want to preach at me?

ELENA
No.
He's giving you a chance you absolutely do not deserve.

Derek studies Caleb for a beat.
Then his expression hardens.

DEREK
Mercy is for people who lose.

In one violent move, Derek stomps on Cody's foot and throws his shoulder into Malcolm.
They lose their grip.
Derek tears free and sprints to the corridor control panel.

Derek slams his palm against the controls.
The LASER GRID roars back to life between him and the team.

DEREK
You still don't get it, Caleb.
Love is what makes people weak.

He backs toward the far exit.
A warning alarm CHIRPS.
Another bank of lasers ignites behind him, trapping him in a narrowing cage of red light.

CODY
Uh... that's not normal.

MALCOLM
He armed the containment cycle.

ELENA
Good.
Let it close on him.

For the first time, Derek looks unsure.
He turns, boxed in by the glowing grid.

DEREK
Shut it down!

MALCOLM
Now you want help?

Caleb steps toward the lasers.

CALEB
This is the moment.
Jesus said, "Love your enemies and pray for those who persecute you."
If we only obey Him when it costs us nothing, that isn't obedience.

He looks at his team.

CALEB (CONT'D)
We heard the Bible story.
Now we decide whether we believe it.

A tense beat.
The lasers HUM louder.

DEREK
Caleb!

CALEB
Cody, give me a three-second opening through the center.
Malcolm, drop the rear bank.
Elena, kill the side rails on my mark.

They hesitate.
Then, one by one, they move.

CODY
Center lane ready.

MALCOLM
Rear bank standing by.

ELENA
Side rails on your mark.

CALEB
Mark!

The team works in perfect sequence.
A narrow path opens through the grid.
Caleb slips through, reaches Derek, and yanks him forward.

CALEB (CONT'D)
Move!

ELENA
Side rails coming back in two!

MALCOLM
Rear bank dropping now!

CODY
Caleb, go! Go!

Caleb pulls Derek through the final gap just as the lasers slam shut behind them.
Derek hits the floor, shaken and breathing hard.

DEREK
You guys saved me. After everything I did to you.

CALEB
Believe me, Derek. You aren't alive right now because of any of us. 
It's the Spirit of God within us that saved you.

MALCOLM
2 Timothy 1:7 says, "For God has not given us a spirit of fear and timidity, but of power, love, and self-discipline."

ELENA
And Luke 1:37 says, "For nothing is impossible with God."

CODY
And that includes, loving our enemy.

Caleb offers his hand to pull Derek off the floor.
Derek only pauses a moment before taking the offer.

CALEB
Alright, come on. Let's get you to prison.

DEREK
But what about grace and love and all that?

CALEB
You still have to answer for your crimes.
But at least you know that God loves you and maybe someday, you can learn to love Him the way we do.

DEREK
How do I do that? What do I have to do?

CODY
You can start by shutting down this laser grid for us.

Derek gets up, moves to the laptop, and types.
The LASERS flicker, then finally power down for good.

They all start walking out of the room.

DEREK
Does anyone have a juice box?

MALCOLM
Keep walking.

FADE OUT.

